HEADWORD: Rush-bearing
<hw>Rush"-bear`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of rural
festival at the dedication of a church, when the parishioners brought
rushes to strew the church.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Nares.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

